    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old male presents to the gastroenterology clinic complaining of recurrent, burning abdominal pain, diarrhea, and weight loss for the past few months. He says the pain is not relieved by taking antacids. Laboratory investigations show elevated serum gastrin levels, prompting further evaluation. Endoscopic examination reveals multiple peptic ulcers in the stomach and duodenum. 1) It is associated with MEN 2 syndrome. 2) 60% of the tumors have a malignant potential. 3) It is associated with H. pylori infection. 4) Diarrhea is the second most common clinical manifestation. 5) BAO: MAO ratio > 0.6 is suggestive of Zollinger-Ellison syndrome. Which of the following statements are true regarding this condition?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "1, 2, 3",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "2, 4, 5",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "2, 3, 4",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "1, 4, 5",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. 2, 4, 5",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Abdominal pain</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Due to <strong>peptic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">ulcer</span> (M/C- >90%)</strong>. ZES is suspected if:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ulcers in unusual locations (2nd part of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"280e59e9331692777186f3beac2c41\">duodenum</span> and beyond).</li>\n<li>Refractory to medical therapy.</li>\n<li>Recurrence after acid-reducing surgery.</li>\n<li>Presents with complications like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> and perforation.</li>\n<li>It is <strong>not associated</strong> with H. pylori or NSAID intake. <strong>(Statement 3)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Diarrhea</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Second <strong>most common</strong> (70%) clinical manifestation.</p>\n<p>Causes are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8dcd91eadf1692777193a72a442f37\">multifactorial</span> and occur due to: <strong>(Statement 4)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Marked volume <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d02a99d051692777194aa3375023b\">overload</span> to the small bowel.</li>\n<li>Inactivation of pancreatic enzymes by the acid.</li>\n<li>Damage to the intestinal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53782f88d31692777187177cb73b24\">epithelium</span> by the acid (can cause <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"819ebcc6691692777191f968d41a03\">malabsorption</span> and weight loss).</li>\n<li>Diarrhea can also be <strong>secretory</strong> due to the direct <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e33367d4a31692777199bb835a83ea\">stimulatory</span> effect of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"212d9c968716927771888fdde3c211\">gastrin</span> on the enterocytes.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Association with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e48bb8abfa1692777192e3fa06774f\">MEN</span> 1 syndrome</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>25% of the cases can be associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e48bb8abfa1692777192e3fa06774f\">MEN</span> 1.</li>\n<li>ZES has a more <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2c27fdf0ed1692777190530a17c849\">indolent</span> course in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e48bb8abfa1692777192e3fa06774f\">MEN</span> 1, and the gastrinomas tend to be smaller, multiple, and located in the duodenal wall more often. <strong>(Statement 1)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:75%\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Gastric pH</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>< 3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Serum <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"212d9c968716927771888fdde3c211\">gastrin</span> </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>>1000 pg/ml</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Secretin <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f3792072b1692777199fd8e2c4f59\">stimulation</span> test (most sensitive and specific <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"212d9c968716927771888fdde3c211\">gastrin</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"80806f031b1692777196a8db8c148e\">provocation</span> test)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>An increase in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"212d9c968716927771888fdde3c211\">gastrin</span> of \u2265120 pg within 15 min of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ff46c25d416927771987897f87843\">secretin</span> injection</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>BAO (basal acid output)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>>15 mEq/h</strong> (normal: <5 mEq/h)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>BAO: MAO (maximal acid output) ratio</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Increased (<strong>>0.6</strong>) <strong>(Statement 5)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Localization of the tumour</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>CT or MRI</li>\n<li>Endoscopic ultrasound</li>\n<li><strong>PET-CT with </strong><strong><sup>68</sup></strong><strong>Ga-DOTATATE</strong> (sensitivity & <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e70dd3ea9916927771988faba61d64\">specificity</span> is >90%)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
